#Text=The Regime ' hacks 711chan.org in response to ' Anonymous ' attack on Scientology ; takes web site off line
#Text=Sunday , January 27 , 2008
#Text=Wikinews has learned that a new entity calling itself
#Text=The Regime used keylogging to gain an administrator password to 711chan.org , a site popular with the open vigilante group " Anonymous " that has recently been attacking Scientology online .
#Text=This website has been deleted due to copyright claims from the Church of Scientology . — Message at 711chan.org as of 9:57 p.m. EST on Saturday .

#Text=At 9:57 p.m. ( eastern time ) the site 711chan.org , was replaced , allegedly by The Regime by the title Church of Scientology along with a statement on the home page stating " This website has been deleted due to copyright claims from the Church of Scientology .

#Text=The Regime 's first attack went along with a message posted to 711chan 's website ( quoted below ) saying that  This site has not been blessed by The Regime and is deemed lame " , believing Anonymous to be self-proclaimed hackers ( although this title was primarily used by the media ) .

column1: #Text=It also refers to Anonymous ' attempt to bring down the Church of Scientology ( named ' Operation Chanology ' ) , saying that " chanology is lame , scientology is lame " .
#Text=It thereafter declared that the message board where Anonymous had been discussing Operation Chanology had been removed .
#Text=Minutes later , 711chan stopped responding to queries .
#Text=The legitimate administrators of 711chan regained control after only three minutes , but it took nearly six hours to restore the site with recent additions missing .

#Text=However , The Regime took the site down again twelve hours later , claiming to have removed the backups and stating , " all your db are belong to us " ( an allusion to the phrase " all your base are belong to us " ) .
#Text=A new video posted to YouTube by someone who claimed to be The Regime shows a logo and uses a computer animated voice to threaten 711chan.org and their affiliates .
#Text=The Regime , however , denies making the video saying " we are in no way responsible for making , nor are we tied to that video in any way .

#Text=—  Re : Message to Scientology " , video posted to YouTube .

column1: #Text=The acronyms in the text description are Scientology jargon " suppressive person " ( a person who criticizes Scientology ) and Scientology founder L. Ron Hubbard .
#Text=Both terms were also used recently in a leaked internal Church of Scientology video featuring Tom Cruise promoting his beliefs .
#Text=The video goes on to state that " Anonymous " has been declared " Fair Game " ( another Scientology term ) .
#Text=The title of The Regime video , " Re : Message to Scientology " , is a reference to the video " Message to Scientology " , which was posted by " Anonymous " to YouTube on Monday .
